PN,31202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1775639132
OL,3,CFirst ever photograph of the far-side
OL,4,Cof the moon released
OL,6,FThe Artemis II astronauts are on their
OL,7,Fway back to Earth from the moon after
OL,8,Fgoing deeper into space than any
OL,9,Fhumans have ever gone before.
OL,11,FThe Orion spacecraft travelled a
OL,12,Frecord-breaking 252,756 miles
OL,13,F(406,771km) away from Earth on Monday
OL,14,Fevening, becoming so close to the moon
OL,15,Fit appeared to them the size of a
OL,16,Fbasketball held at arm's length, Nasa
OL,17,Fsaid.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1775639132
OL,3,CFirst ever photograph of the far-side
OL,4,Cof the moon released
OL,6,FThis is not the first image of the far-
OL,7,Fside of the moon ever, but it is the
OL,8,Ffirst photograph of it to have been
OL,9,Ftaken by a human.
OL,11,FIn 1959, the Lunar 3 spacecraft
OL,12,Flaunched from Kazakhstan and reached
OL,13,Fthe moon, capturing and sending back
OL,14,Fgrainy images of that part of its
OL,15,Fsurface.
OL,17,FHowever, the astronauts were the first
OL,18,Fhumans to see some parts of the moon's
OL,19,Ffar side.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1775639132
OL,3,CFirst ever photograph of the far-side
OL,4,Cof the moon released
OL,6,FAs planned, the Artemis II crew lost
OL,7,Fcontact with Earth for around 40
OL,8,Fminutes during their journey behind
OL,9,Fthe moon.
OL,11,FAfter seeing the far-side, the crew
OL,12,Fthen entered a period where the moon
OL,13,Feclipsed the sun before making their
OL,14,Fjourney back to Earth, with Mercury,
OL,15,FVenus, Mars and Saturn visible during
OL,16,Fthe darkness.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
